Halve @brioche buns{4}. Form @ground beef{20%ounce} into four equal-size patties, each slightly wider than the buns; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Grill ==

Heat a well-oiled #grill{} or #grill pan{} to medium-high heat. Cook burgers to desired doneness (we suggest ~{3-5%minutes} per side, but grills can vary). In the last ~{2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with @cheddar cheese{8%ounce}; cover and cook until cheese melts. Add buns; toast until golden. Fill buns with burgers and serve.

== Stovetop ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook burgers to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. In the last ~{2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with cheddar; cover and cook until cheese melts. Toast buns in burger drippings if desired. Fill buns with burgers and serve.

> Build your perfect burger just the way you like it!
> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°

== Recipe Suggestion ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @?Dijon mustard{}, @?ketchup{}, and @?mayonnaise{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste, then slather it on your burger buns.